entry.title: Brief Introduction - Thu Sep 21
entry.content:
Hi I’m Looloo. I’ll be your supplemental Instruction (SI) Leader for this quarter. I am a proud member of this great organization called SCAA (Student Center for Academic Achievement).

I took CS 3560 Introduction to Systems Programming with Professor Stalica Summer 2017 quarter. Professor Stalica is extremely awesome, super chill and helpful. I really look forward to work with him to help you learn and succeed in this course.

Throughout this quarter, I will put up discussion session materials on this website.

About myself, I am a graduate student in Computer Science. This is my third quarter at CSUEB. I took my Data Structures and Algorithms Spring 2017 quarter with Dr. Varick Erickson. If you would like to know more about me, feel free to click on the About tab.

I will be hosting discussion session twice a week (one discussion session per lecture). Around Midterm and Final, I will also be hosting extra review sessions to help you prepare for the exams.
